Your rather lengthy post is a good one.  I respect what you did for so many.  I feel that you have great license to speak for Rear Echelon personnel who experienced some tough times.. but you did not have to hump the bush.  You saw the results of conflict but I don't believe that you witnessed the killing or participated in the killing.  As a woman and certainly as a lady, Vietnam was a different experience for you than it was for me.  As a non-combatant your service can not be disregarded or played down.. but there is a serious difference in your contribution and mine.<br>
Be a good spokesman(person) for yourself and not the rest of us.<br><br>
Welcome Home Lady<br><br>
MTF-anymouse-Humming Eagle-Tatekohomni Wambli<br><br>
P.S  I can forgive sometimes... but I will never forget!
